      <h2>What Is This?</h2>
      <p>
        Epstein Transparency Act is a factual, noise-free database tracking
        developments around the Epstein Files and the Epstein Transparency Act.
        We aggregate reporting from major news outlets and present it in a
        clear, searchable format.
      </p>

      <h2>Our Approach</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Pure aggregation.</strong> We summarize and link to original reporting from
          outlets like Reuters, AP, NYT, BBC, and The Guardian. No opinion or commentary.</li>
        <li><strong>Source attribution.</strong> Every article links back to its original source.
          We do not claim to produce original reporting.</li>
        <li><strong>People database.</strong> We maintain profiles of individuals named in
          documents, officials, and other connected parties, with bidirectional
          links to relevant news coverage.</li>
        <li><strong>Timeline.</strong> A chronological record of key events in the case.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        This site aggregates publicly available reporting from established news
        outlets. Inclusion of any individual in the people database does not
        imply guilt or wrongdoing. All information is sourced from public records
        and published reporting.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
